ce:section.ce:para:
The SEM images of as-prepared BiVO4, Ag3PO4 and BiVO4/N-CQDs/Ag3PO4 hybrid materials are presented in Fig. 4
                        . As shown in Fig. 4a and d, BiVO4 presents plate-like structure and stacked together. Fig. 4b and e show the SEM images of the pure Ag3PO4. The as-prepared Ag3PO4 powder shows sphere-like structures and aggregated with each other. In the BiVO4/N-CQDs/Ag3PO4 sample (Fig. 4c and f), both BiVO4 and Ag3PO4 can be found. Furthermore, the Ag3PO4 nanoparticles were loaded in the gap of the plate-like BiVO4, indicating good affinity between these materials. However, the N-CQDs were difficult to be distinguished by SEM, the reason can be attributed to their very small size [35,45]. Additionally, the EDS mapping of the BiVO4/N-CQDs/Ag3PO4 hybrid materials was also performed (Fig. 5
                        ). The results further confirmed the presence of Bi, V, O, Ag, P, N and C elements in BiVO4/N-CQDs/Ag3PO4 hybrid materials, which strongly demonstrate the successful preparation of BiVO4/N-CQDs/Ag3PO4 hybrid materials.
